      <hedline>
        <hl1>June 11-17; Loophole in Arms Treaty</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ERIC SCHMITT</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Administration lawyers have provided President Clinton with a new legal interpretation of a 1972 arms control treaty with Russia that could allow him to begin building the first phase of a national missile defense without violating the accord.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Administration lawyers have provided President Clinton with a new legal interpretation of a 1972 arms control treaty with Russia that could allow him to begin building the first phase of a national missile defense without violating the accord.</p>
        <p>The new interpretation, drafted at the White House's request, offers a way for Mr. Clinton to avoid breaching the Antiballistic Missile Treaty, a prospect that has already threatened to undercut relations with Russia and European allies.</p>
        <p>ERIC SCHMITT</p>
      </block>
